{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51cdbced-2196-4978-be98-8c8a691d3704","content":"You're all set. Run your tests in hot-reload mode with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a watch-style session. When a test fails, you edit the source code (test or production code), save the file, and the runner automatically re-executes the affected tests **without a full rebuild**. The feedback loop is nearly instant.\n\n**Tips:**\n- Filter to specific failing tests with `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~YourTestName\"` to reduce noise.\n- The session stays alive until you press `Ctrl+C`.\n- Hot reload applies your edits via delta/metadata updates, so most code changes apply immediately (method body changes, lambdas, etc.). Structural changes (new classes, signature changes) may trigger a full rebuild automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f912ec0f-c85d-4929-ba26-1aef93343e07","outputTokens":179,"requestId":"BC33:BD0FA:1DD3ECA:21192C2:69FA9802"},"id":"a293c8b0-ec9a-44ac-ab93-9626f9a4782b","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:23:22.629Z","parentId":"dd2338ab-af5b-4312-b3ab-e6dd5dfb8969"}
